  "answer": "A) Cytokines are polypeptide hormones. Humans release hormones in several chemical categories, including polypeptides (e.g., cytokines, glucagon, and insulin), amino acids (e.g., epinephrine, serotonin, and histamine), and fatty acids (e.g., glucocorticoids, prostaglandins, and leukotrienes). There are no carbohydrate hormones. (See Schwartz 9th ed., p. 17.)",
