  "answer": "C) First line therapy for ITP in adults is corticosteroids and IV immunoglobulin. Splenectomy is second line therapy. Desmopressin is not used in the treatment of ITP. (See Schwartz 9th ed., pp 72-73, and Table 4-2.)",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
