  "answer": "D) Fluoroquinolone plus either metronidazole or clindamycin (for anaerobic coverage) is indicated in penicillin allergic patients undergoing biliary tract surgery with active infection (Table 6-2). (See Schwartz 9th ed., p. 119.)",
