  "answer": "D) The most common histologic types of soft tissue sarcoma in adults (excluding Kaposi’s sarcoma) are malignant fibrous histiocytoma (28%), leiomyosarcoma (12%), liposarcoma (15%), synovial sarcoma (10%), and malignant peripheral nerve sheath tumors (6%). (See Schwartz 9th ed., p 1284, and Table 36-1.)",
