  "answer": "C) ASDs can be classified into three different types: (a) sinus venosus defects, comprising approximately 5 to 10% of all ASDs; (b) ostiumprimumdefects, which are more correctly described as partial AV canal defects; and (c) ostium secundum defects, which are the most prevalent subtype, comprising 80% of all ASDs. Ostium secundum defects are due to defects of the septum primum and those situated within the fossa ovalis. The secundum defects therefore included patent foramen ovales. (See Schwartz 9th ed., p 592.) Ostium secundum defects are due to defects of the septum primum and those situated within the fossa ovalis. The secundumdefects therefore include patent foramen ovales.",
