  "answer": "A) Autogenous vein is superior to prosthetic conduits for all infrainguinal bypasses, even in the above-knee (AK) position. This preference is applicable not only for the initial bypass but also for reoperative cases. For long bypasses, ipsilateral great saphenous vein (GSV), contralateral GSV, small saphenous vein, arm vein, and spliced vein are used, in decreasing order of preference. (See Schwartz 9th ed., p 765.)",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
