  "question": "The average annual growth of abdominal aortic aneurysms is approximately",
  "options": {
    "A": "1 mm",
    "B": "3 mm",
    "C": "1 cm",
    "D": "3 cm"
  },
  "answer": "B) The natural history of an abdominal aortic aneurysm(AAA) is to expand and rupture. AAAexhibits a ‘staccato’ pattern of growth, where periods of relative quiescence may alternate with expansion. Therefore, although an individual pattern of growth cannot be predicted, average aggregate growth is approximately 3 to 4 mm/y. There is some evidence to suggest that larger aneurysms may expand faster than smaller aneurysms, but there is significant overlap between the ranges of growth rates at each strata of size. (See Schwartz 9th ed., p 723.)",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
