  "answer": "C) Insulinomas are the most common pancreatic endocrine neoplasms and present with a typical clinical syndrome known as Whipple’s triad. The triad consists of symptomatic fasting hypoglycemia, a documented serumglucose level 50 mg/dL, and relief of symptoms with the administration of glucose. (See Schwartz 9th ed., p 1217.)",
