  "answer": "C) Aldosterone functions mainly to increase sodium reabsorption and potassium and hydrogen ion excretion at the level of the renal distal convoluted tubule. Less commonly, aldosterone increases sodiumabsorption in salivary glands and GI mucosal surfaces. (See Schwartz 9th ed., p 1390.)",
  "chapter": "General Surgery",
